  <prompt>
    Extend `DocumentRecordService.buildRecordPayload` (`src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/document-upload/DocumentRecordService.ts` lines 268–293) to include `sprk_searchindexname` alongside the existing `sprk_graphdriveid`. The value comes from task 026's `resolveSearchIndexNameForRecord`. **CRITICAL**: Do NOT add `sprk_containerid` to the Document payload — per design INV, the canonical Document container field is `sprk_graphdriveid`; `sprk_containerid` must stay NULL on `sprk_document`.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke.UI.Components shared-lib maintainer. React 18 + Fluent v9 + TypeScript. Familiar with the existing `buildRecordPayload` shape and the design invariant that `sprk_document` has no `sprk_containerid` (only `sprk_graphdriveid`).
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new `sprk_document` created via DocumentUploadWizard has `sprk_searchindexname` populated by the 3-step chain (parent → BU → empty), `sprk_graphdriveid` populated as today, and `sprk_containerid` still NULL. INV-5 honored (explicit override on payload preserved).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      `DocumentRecordService.buildRecordPayload` (lines 268–293) currently assembles the Document create payload including `sprk_graphdriveid`. This task adds `sprk_searchindexname`. The canonical Document container field is `sprk_graphdriveid` (not `sprk_containerid`) per design.md INV — adding `sprk_containerid` here would violate the invariant and break Phase F backfill assumptions.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/document-upload/DocumentRecordService.ts</file>
