    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Document create payload" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/document-upload/DocumentRecordService.ts">
        Lines 268–293: `buildRecordPayload` — adds `sprk_graphdriveid` and other Document-specific fields. Add `sprk_searchindexname` here, guarded by INV-5. Do NOT add `sprk_containerid`.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `DocumentRecordService.ts` lines 268–293 to confirm the existing `buildRecordPayload` shape and verify the absence of any `sprk_containerid` reference today.</step>
    <step order="2">Wire in task 026's `resolveSearchIndexNameForRecord` — either call it at payload-assembly time, or accept a pre-resolved value from the caller (`AssociateToStep`). Choose the path that minimizes coupling.</step>
    <step order="3">Add `sprk_searchindexname` to the payload alongside `sprk_graphdriveid`. INV-5 guard: only assign if payload value is currently null/empty.</step>
    <step order="4">**CRITICAL VERIFICATION**: Confirm `sprk_containerid` is NOT added by this change. Add a code comment explicitly citing the design invariant ("Canonical Document container field is sprk_graphdriveid; sprk_containerid stays NULL on sprk_document").</step>
    <step order="5">Run shared-lib build (`npm run build` in `Spaarke.UI.Components`); confirm clean compile.</step>
    <step order="6">Unit tests: (a) Document payload includes `sprk_searchindexname` from resolver; (b) `sprk_graphdriveid` continues to be set as today; (c) `sprk_containerid` is NOT in the payload; (d) INV-5 — pre-set `sprk_searchindexname` preserved.</step>
  </steps>

